=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Address => L<Paws::PartnerCentralSelling::AddressSummary>

Specifies the end C<Customer>'s address details associated with the
C<Opportunity>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CompanyName => Str

Specifies the end C<Customer>'s company name associated with the
C<Opportunity>.


=head2 Industry => Str

Specifies which industry the end C<Customer> belongs to associated with
the C<Opportunity>. It refers to the category or sector that the
customer's business operates in.

To submit a value outside the picklist, use C<Other>.

Conditionally mandatory if C<Other> is selected for Industry Vertical
in LOVs.


=head2 OtherIndustry => Str

Specifies the end C<Customer>'s industry associated with the C<
Opportunity>, when the selected value in the C<Industry> field is
C<Other>. This field is relevant when the customer's industry doesn't
fall under the predefined picklist values and requires a custom
description.


=head2 WebsiteUrl => Str

Specifies the end customer's company website URL associated with the
C<Opportunity>. This value is crucial to map the customer within the
Amazon Web Services CRM system.



